He says well there are three rods the bodily rod the verbal rod and the mental rod and is the bodily rod one thing the verbal rod another and the mental rod another thing more he says yes they are all three different things all these three rods

30
00:03:56,432 --> 00:04:18,762
says the Buddha, thus analysed, thus differentiated, which rod does the Nīgānta-nāta-putta, that's his correct name as the Jain leader, describe as the most greatly blameworthy for the making of evil kamma, the production of evil kamma, the bodily rod, the verbal rod or the mental rod.

31
00:04:19,062 --> 00:04:28,802
The Nigantha replies that the bodily rod is the most greatly blameworthy for the making of evil karma.

32
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:35,677
The production of evil karma, not so much the verbal rod, not so much the mental rod.

33
00:04:35,718 --> 00:04:43,309
Now you get this little bit of repartee, which it seems in those days, you got the person to repeat what they said three times.

34
00:04:43,668 --> 00:04:46,353
So they couldn't say, I didn't say that.

35
00:04:46,372 --> 00:04:46,733
Okay.

36
00:04:47,574 --> 00:04:49,918
So did you say the bodily rod?

37
00:04:50,077 --> 00:04:54,603
I say the bodily rod, friend Gautama.

38
00:04:54,584 --> 00:05:21,992
do you say the bodily rod eager to pass him i say bodily rod friend gotama do you say bodily rod digger to pass him i say bodily rod friend gotama now i should think it was just a little bit more repartee like you know like are you sure it's the bodily rod i'm absolutely sure is this what your teacher told you it is etc so now having stated his position

