similes on how he's going to treat the Buddha.

74
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:29,858
He says, just as a strong man seizing a long-haired ram by the hair would drag him to and drag him fro and drag him all around in the same way, I, statement by statement, will drag Gautama the contemplative to and drag him fro and drag him all around.

75
00:08:30,379 --> 00:08:36,408
And then he gives more and more sort of similes of how he's going to treat this poor

76
